    <stitle>FRAME - BOLT AND TORQUE INFORMATION - HUCKBOLT FASTENERS (HP 8)</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="6">
        <title>HUCKBOLT FASTENERS (HP 8)</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Refer to the
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0100123">Figure</hotlnk>
                below.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0100123" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg01/G0100123.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px"/>
                <caption>Figure 7. Huckbolt Fasteners</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>Huckbolt HP 8 fasteners are used in various positions in frame rail construction. Advantages to this
                style fastener are consistent clamp load and a high resistance to loosening due to vibration. The need
                to recheck fastener torque is eliminated.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Removal</title>
            <para>The swaged collar cannot be unscrewed due to the locking grooves on the HP 8 fastener. Removal
                requires a Huck Collar Cutter or the
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0100124">collar can be split with an air chisel</hotlnk>
                while supporting the opposite side of the collar
                <xref refid="f0100124"/>. When the collar is split, the fastener can be driven out with a punch.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0100124" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg01/G0100124.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 8. Collar Can Be Split With an Air Chisel</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>The HP 8 fastener is not intended for re-use. To do so can result in damage to the vehicle
                        frame or components attached to the frame.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>In the event that Huck fasteners are removed, in order to retain the same joint integrity,
                        International requires that new Huck fasteners be used for attachment/reattachment of
                        components.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Installation</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Huckbolt HP 8 fasteners cannot be installed without Huck installation equipment.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the HP 8 fastener into the component and frame hole.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0100125">Place the collar over the fastener pintail
                        <xref refid="f0100125"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0100125" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg01/G0100125.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="192px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 9. Place Collar Over Fastener Pintail</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0100126">Place the Huck installation tool over the HP 8 fastener pintail
                        <xref refid="f0100126"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0100126" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg01/G0100126.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 10. Place Installation Tool Over Fastener Pintail</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Activate the Huck installation tool.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The Huck installation tool creates a pulling force on the fastener, seating the bolt head and
                        closing the gap between the mating surfaces. The collar is swaged into the pintail locking
                        grooves
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0100127">developing clamping force
                            <xref refid="f0100127"/>
                        </hotlnk>
                        . As pulling forces further increase, the
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0100128">body of the fastener separates at the breakneck
                            <xref refid="f0100128"/>
                        </hotlnk>
                        , completing installation.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f0100127" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg01/G0100127.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 11. Clamping Force is Developed</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0100128" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg01/G0100128.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 12. Body of Fastener Separates at Breakneck</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
